    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i've been seeing these intermittent \"Connection Reset by Peer\" errors in our production EC2 instances on AWS. it's not constant, just happens every few hours. \n\nhere's a snippet from the CloudWatch logs:\n2023-10-27T14:22:01Z ERROR [connection-handler] remote peer closed connection unexpectedly: Connection reset by peer (errno: 104)\n2023-10-27T14:25:44Z ERROR [connection-handler] remote peer closed connection unexpectedly: Connection reset by peer (errno: 104)\n\ncould this be an issue with our security group configs or something else in the VPC setup?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While security groups can cause connection issues, the \"Connection reset by peer\" error (errno: 104) often points to an issue on the *other* end of the connection, not necessarily the networking infrastructure itself. It usually means the remote server or client abruptly terminated the session. You should investigate application-level timeouts, load balancer health checks, or network device timeouts between your EC2 instance and the peer.",
      "source": "target",
